Java Programmer
Responsibilities
Will be expected to analyze, design, plan, develop code and unit test functions/modules of an application. Work collaboratively with other members of the project team and the project manager to ensure deadlines and high quality delivery of the application in line with customer’s business requirements. He or she will be familiar and confident in performing the following roles as a member of a group of software engineers in a project: Analyze and design the function/modules of an application system that is being assignedPlanning the development of the code needed to perform the function/modulesDevelop and unit test application code that will provide such function/modules according to the specifications using recommended process, standards and toolsAs appropriate, develop and maintain proper defined documentation necessary to maintain and support the applicationStrict adherence and application of configuration management procedures for changes to application systemProvide necessary support to other team members as required to help deliver systems on schedule and with high quality RequirementsBachelors or Masters in Software engineering or ITExperience in Java, J2EE technologies such as Tomcat, JBoss, EJB, Struts, POJOsExpertise in Object Oriented technologies using Java, J2EE, JSP/Servlet, JDBC API, EJB.Sound knowledge of frameworks like Struts or Hibernate.Experience in IDEs such as EclipseExperience in software configuration management such as Clear case, CVS, SVNGood working knowledge of SQL/PLSQLExperience with Web ServicesGood working knowledge of Linux or UnixAbility to work independentlyApprox. 2- 4 years experienceSelf-motivated and good project management, interpersonal & communication skillsAbility to communicate in English is preferred
